      "content": "On request of some of the group members sharing a post that I had written 2 days ago. \n*long post but pls read it slowly - do no rush thru it*\u00f0\u009f\u0099\u008f\n\n*one track life*\nHappiness and life events shud run on different tracks \n\nHappiness should not depend on life events \n\nThings go as per yr wish it makes u happy things don't go as per yr wish/plans makes u sad - a very avg way to lead life \n\nAlternate \nU r in always in a state of happiness \n\nDesired outcomes - Happy with faith in God\nAdverse outcomes - Happy with faith in God\n\nAn example - M S Dhoni\n\n*How to achieve this level of equanimity*\n\nThru self control \n\n*How to achieve self control*\n\nBy focussing on 4 most critical life processes \n\n1. Breathing \n2. Drinking \n3. Eating \n4. Sleeping \n\n*How to improve the se processes*\n\nBreathing thru yoga, cardiac exercise, morning walk, surya kriya. \n\nDrinking 3-4 litres of water daily and not drinking water which is more than 5 degrees below normal temperature. \n\nEating restrict number of meals per day 2  to max 3.\nLimiting the eating window to 10 hours max - 8 am to 6 pm, 9 am to 7 pm, 10 am to 8 pm\nThe less processed the food is better it is. \n\nSleep: sleep by btwn 9 (early) 11 (latest) \nGet up 4 (v early) 6 (latest) \n\n*Others things to do to bring self/impulse control*\n\nReduce the gap between getting up and taking bath to least \nAt least 30 mins for physical health - yoga, walking, \nAt least 30 mins for mental health - puja, aarti, meditation, reading.",
